                <p>
                    The Committee Member acknowledges and agrees that any and all nonpublic information of whatever kind or nature relating to this Agreement, or nonpublic information that the Committee Member acquires in connection with or as a result of this Agreement, or nonpublic information that the Committee Member receives or becomes aware of during the term of this Agreement concerning the Company, its clients, and other third parties, is confidential and proprietary ("Confidential Information"). Confidential Information shall include information marked as “Proprietary”, “Confidential”, or with a similar legend. In the absence of any marking, Confidential Information shall also include all information that a reasonable person would consider to be confidential. The Committee Member will use Confidential Information only for the purposes of this Agreement. The Committee Member shall not share Confidential Information with anyone except such persons expressly authorized to receive such information in connection with the performance of this Agreement (i.e., others designated to participate in the same peer review process). The Committee Member will not duplicate Confidential Information, or use it at any time to provide, perform, or furnish any services; or use it to invent, create, modify, adapt, or manufacture any products for the benefit of the Committee Member or any third party.
                </p>
                <p>
                    If the Committee Member requires administrative assistance for the performance of obligations under this Agreement, he/she will limit access to Confidential Information only to those administrative assistants who have a legitimate need for access to perform this Agreement. The Committee Member will ensure that any assistant is aware of and agrees in writing to comply with the confidentiality restrictions of this Agreement.
                </p>
                <p>
                    By execution of this agreement, Committee Member acknowledges that the unauthorized disclosure or use of
                    Confidential and Proprietary Information as described in the “Non-Disclosure Agreement for the CPRIT Scientific
                    Research and Prevention Program (SRPP) Committee Members,” which the Committee Member has signed and is
